# Calendar and Scheduling

## CalendarKit Basic setup

- Pinned version: `calendarkit-basic` (MIT, npm)
- **Only** [`CalendarView.tsx`](src/features/calendar-scheduling/components/calendar/CalendarView.tsx) imports `calendarkit-basic` — feature tabs consume the wrapper
- **Views available:** `month`, `week`, `day` only (no agenda, resource/timeline, drag-drop, or RRULE in Basic)
- **Staff scheduling:** week view + `calendars` filter toggles per staff (resource view requires Pro)
- **Reschedule:** click booking → `BookingDetailsSheet` → `RescheduleDialog` (no drag-drop in Basic)
- **Week start:** Monday (`weekStartsOn={1}`)

## Data flow

- Calendar event data **always** flows through TanStack Query hooks in `calendar-scheduling/hooks/`
- Calendar components **never** fetch directly — receive domain `ScheduleEvent[]` as props from query results
- Map domain events to CalendarKit `Date`-based events in the wrapper via `lib/adapters/to-kit-event.ts`
- API functions in `calendar-scheduling/api/` use fixtures + `mockDelay` until backend is live

## Feature placement

- All calendar UI, hooks, types, and API live under `src/features/calendar-scheduling/` — do not split across other features
